// corridor content — the placed objects of the 2.5D rail traverse (its place/
// bounds/camera live in the level manifest). The corridor runs along world X
// (the rail axis); the rail centreline is world Z = 0. Walls/props are spaced
// along X to give the side-on framing depth cues + parallax as the avatar walks.
// The avatar is a single persistent entity seeded by the level's entry zone
// (atrium), not authored per zone (#27 seamless streaming) — so the corridor
// authors no avatar; the player carries in from the atrium.
Zone(instances: [
    // A lone patroller pacing the corridor along X (a light threat on the rest
    // beat). Freeform — marked LEVEL_OBJECTIVE (`flags: Some(2)`): it doesn't gate
    // this zone, it contributes to the *level* objective that opens the level exit
    // (#27 tier 2). path[0] == spawn.
    Use(name: "patroller", pos: (1.6, 0.0, 0.0), flags: Some(2), path: [(1.6, 0.0), (0.4, 0.0)]),
    // Walls / props lining the rail.
    Use(name: "landmark_block", pos: (-0.8, 0.0, -0.5)),
    Use(name: "landmark_block", pos: (0.6, 0.0, -0.5), rot: Some((0.0, 0.3, 0.0))),
])
